qas.question: Nwankwo Kanu won what honor twice?
Nwankwo Kanu won in what championship league?

context: The nation's cadet team from Japan '93 produced some international players notably Nwankwo Kanu, a two-time <a0_0>African Footballer of the year<a0_0/> who won the <a1_0>European Champions League<a1_0/> with Ajax Amsterdam and later played with <a2_0>Inter Milan, Arsenal<a2_0/>, West Bromwich Albion and Portsmouth. Other players that graduated from the junior teams are Nduka Ugbade, Jonathan Akpoborie, Victor Ikpeba, Celestine Babayaro, Wilson Oruma and Taye Taiwo. Some other famous Nigerian footballers include John Obi Mikel, Obafemi Martins, Vincent Enyeama, Yakubu Aiyegbeni, Rashidi Yekini, Peter Odemwingie and Jay-Jay Okocha.
